{"metadata":{"objective":"Rebutting an argument","lastStepAudioPath":"summary","audioPath":"CS28CCT3/3/Refresher"},"steps":[{"headerText":"","leftText":"<p><span class=\"ju-cktitle\" style=\"color:#025B5B;font-family:lato,sans-serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:bold;\">Esprit argues back</span><br /><br />Mr. Aplomb is suing his next door neighbor Ms. Esprit for making too much noise.&nbsp; But now it&#39;s Ms. Esprit&#39;s turn to present her side.&nbsp; As the law reporter, you need to help your readers understand how Ms. Esprit will rebut Mr. Aplomb&#39;s argument.&nbsp;<br /><br /><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\"><strong>Mr. Aplomb&#39;s argument and evidence:</strong></span><br /><br /><span class=\"ju-examples\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:tahoma;\">Ms. Esprit should not create disturbances with loud parties and noisy animals that make it impossible for me to sleep, because it is reasonable to expect peace and quiet in your own house.&nbsp; Local ordinances prohibit making noises that are above a certain decibel level.&nbsp; Furthermore, when people buy property they expect to be able to enjoy it.&nbsp; Finally, according to the respected Doctor Kronkheit, medical science shows that if people do not get enough sleep, they cannot function in their daily lives.</span><br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img alt=\"An illustration shows Mr. Aplomb and Ms. Esprit presenting their case to a judge.  Ms. Esprit is explaining why Mr. Aplomb is wrong.\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p>","settings":{"showHeader":0,"showAudio":1,"audioPath":"1","hideRightPanel":0,"showNext":1,"delayStep":"0","delayRight":"0"}},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":1,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"2"},"leftText":"<p>A <strong>rebuttal</strong> (or <strong>counter-argument)</strong> is a type of argument used to challenge the original argument.<br /><br />To prepare her rebuttal, Ms. Esprit&#39;s first step is to look for any weaknesses in Mr. Aplomb&#39;s argument.&nbsp; She can look for flaws or gaps in his data, attack his logic, or discredit his expert opinion.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><img alt=\"A diagram shows three stages of an argument: the argument, the rebuttal, and the counter-rebuttal.   In the argument stage, Mr. Aplomb makes his argument.  In the rebuttal stage, Ms. Esprit attacks the argument. In the counter-rebuttal stage, Mr. Aplomb attacks the rebuttal and supports the argument.  This mini-lesson is about the rebuttal stage in which Ms. Esprit attacks Mr. Aplomb's argument.\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p>","headerText":"What does Ms. Esprit need to do to prepare her rebuttal?"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":"0","audioPath":"3"},"rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Ms. Esprit&#39;s rebuttal:</span></p><p>The noise ordinance only applies after midnight on weekdays and after 1:00 a.m. on weekends.</p>","leftText":"<p>Here is one part of Mr. Aplomb&#39;s argument:&nbsp;<br /><br /><span class=\"ju-examples\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:tahoma;\">Local ordinances prohibit making noises that are above a certain decibel level.</span><br /><br />Ms. Esprit finds that this data is correct but there are gaps in the factual details.<br />&nbsp;</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":"0","audioPath":"4"},"leftText":"<p>Here is another part of Mr. Aplomb&#39;s argument:<br /><br /><span class=\"ju-examples\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:tahoma;\">When people buy property they expect to be able to enjoy it.</span><br /><br />Ms. Esprit finds a weakness in this logic.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Ms. Esprit&#39;s rebuttal:</span></p><p>This argument goes both ways:&nbsp; Other people have the right to enjoy their property, too.</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":"0","audioPath":"5"},"leftText":"<p>Here is the final part of Mr. Aplomb&#39;s argument:<br /><br /><span class=\"ju-examples\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:tahoma;\">According to the respected Doctor Kronkheit, medical science shows that if people do not get enough sleep, they cannot function in their daily lives.&nbsp;</span><br /><br />To discredit Mr. Aplomb&#39;s argument, Ms. Esprit finds her own expert<em> </em>with a different opinion.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Ms. Esprit&#39;s rebuttal:</span></p><p>Other medical authorities, such as the esteemed Dr. Boop, say that while sleep is one component of good health, enjoying yourself and having fun is also essential to good health.&nbsp;</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":"0","audioPath":"6"},"leftText":"<p>The next step is to consider other ways to rebut the argument. &nbsp;For example, Ms. Esprit can&nbsp;try to attack Mr. Aplomb&#39;s&nbsp;reason for his argument (the <em>because</em>).&nbsp;<br /><br />Mr. Aplomb&#39;s reason is this:<br /><br /><span class=\"ju-examples\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:tahoma;\">It is reasonable to expect peace and quiet in your own house.&nbsp; </span><br /><br />Ms. Esprit attacks Mr. Aplomb&#39;s reason using logic.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Ms. Esprit&#39;s rebuttal:</span></p><p>Really? Living in a community always involves some noise, such as lawnmowers,&nbsp;airplanes overhead, and children playing. &nbsp;It is not reasonable to expect a noise-free environment. &nbsp;</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":1,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":"0","audioPath":"7"},"leftText":"<p>Ms. Esprit can rebut Mr. Aplomb&#39;s argument in different ways: &nbsp;</p><ul><li>She can point out weaknesses in the support for his argument.</li><li>She can introduce new evidence that contradicts Mr. Aplomb&#39;s evidence.</li><li>She can attack the logic of Mr. Aplomb&#39;s claim or reason.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>","rightText":"<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain ju-tight\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\"><strong>Ms. Esprit&#39;s rebuttal:</strong></span></p><p>You do not have the right to sleep without being disturbed, because the noise ordinance only applies after midnight on weekdays and after 1:00 a.m. on weekends.&nbsp; Furthermore, other people have the right to enjoy their property, too.&nbsp; In addition, medical authorities such as the esteemed Dr. Boop say that while sleep is one component of good health, enjoying yourself and having fun is also essential to good health.&nbsp; Finally, living in a community always involves some noise, such as lawnmowers, airplanes overhead, and children playing. &nbsp;It is not reasonable to expect a noise-free environment. &nbsp;</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","headerText":"Putting it all together"}],"overviewHeader":"Overview"}
